

---
const pageTitle = "The Fool";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.94), rgba(245,245,245,0.94)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(10deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.2;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        line-height: 1.05;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-weight: bold;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin: 0 0 24px;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      p { margin: 0 0 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px 16px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #f3f3f3, #ebebeb);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
        font-size: 16px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 4px 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .content-layer p,
      .content-layer h1,
      .content-layer h2,
      .content-layer .subtitle,
      .content-layer .divider,
      .content-layer .quote,
      .content-layer .mini-links,
      .content-layer .footer-note {
        text-shadow: 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        html, body { font-size: 17px; }
        h1 { font-size: 34px; }
        .frame { padding: 18px 16px 24px; }
        .symbol-bg {
          width: 210px;
          height: 210px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">symbols index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/symbols/fire">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/symbols/serpent">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none">
            <g stroke="#000000" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <rect x="88" y="70" width="124" height="160" rx="10" />
              <rect x="100" y="82" width="100" height="136" rx="6" />
              <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="34" />
              <path d="M134 150 C134 136, 142 128, 150 128 C158 128, 166 136, 166 150" />
              <path d="M138 166 C144 172, 156 172, 162 166" />
              <path d="M108 98 L126 116" />
              <path d="M192 98 L174 116" />
              <path d="M108 202 L126 184" />
              <path d="M192 202 L174 184" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>The Fool</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">symbols / play / paradox / archive entry 002</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            The fool appears wherever life refuses to stay trapped inside seriousness.
            He steps outside fixed roles and moves without certainty, which at first
            looks like ignorance but often reveals a deeper kind of freedom.
          </p>

          <p>
            Because he is not bound by the same expectations, the fool can enter
            spaces others avoid. He risks embarrassment, misstep, and misunderstanding,
            but in doing so he remains close to something alive.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            what looks like foolishness from the outside can be the beginning of something real.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">beginning without knowing</h2>

          <p>
            The fool often stands at the start of a path. Not because he knows where
            he is going, but because he is willing to move without guarantees.
          </p>

          <p>
            Psychologically, this symbol appears when an old identity breaks down.
            The familiar way of being no longer works, and something new has not yet
            formed. This space can feel unstable, but it is also where transformation begins.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">play and risk</h2>

          <p>
            The fool carries both danger and possibility. Without awareness, he can
            fall into chaos or denial. But when held consciously, he opens movement
            where life has become rigid.
          </p>

          <p>
            Play is not meaningless here. It is a loosening of structure that allows
            something new to emerge.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">back to symbols index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/serpent">continue to: serpent</a>
            <a class="red" href="/symbols/fire">fire</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>